claim.claim-text:
27. A method for absorbing bodily exudates with an expandable absorbent garment, the method comprising: 
providing said expandable absorbent garment comprising an absorbent composite having a length, opposite ends and opposite side regions and body panels attached to said opposite side regions adjacent said opposite ends of said absorbent composite, said body panels connected to form openings shaped to receive the legs of a user, wherein said absorbent composite comprises a backsheet, a topsheet and a retention portion disposed between said backsheet and said topsheet; 
securing said absorbent garment on said user with said legs of said user extending through said openings; 
expanding said absorbent composite in a lateral direction at said ends of said absorbent composite as said body panels are fitted around the hips of the user while retaining a crotch region of said absorbent composite in an unexpanded configuration; and 
insulting said crotch region of said absorbent composite with said bodily exudates and expanding said crotch region of said absorbent composite as said retention portion absorbs said bodily exudates.

36. A method of assembling an expandable absorbent garment comprising: 
providing an absorbent composite having a length, opposite ends and opposite side regions, wherein said absorbent composite is laterally expandable at least at said opposite ends thereof; 
providing a pair of front body panels having lateral inboard and outboard edges; 
providing a pair of rear body panels having lateral inboard and outboard edges; 
securing said inboard edges of said front body panels to said opposite side regions of said absorbent garment at one of said ends of said absorbent composite; and 
securing said inboard edges of said rear body panels to said opposite side regions of said absorbent garment at said other of said ends of said absorbent composite.
